rows.label: qev055601_MSG0001
rows.name:
Hmm. This could fairly be described as a predicament.
But what to do about it?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0002
rows.name:
I simply cannot understand her motives.
Why would anyone intentionally travel to such a
dangerous place?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0010
rows.name: Query

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0011
rows.name: Ask Nan'celeg what happened.

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0020
rows.name: Comfort

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0021
rows.name:
Tell Nan'celeg that you're happy
to listen to his worries.

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0003
rows.name: My division, Nen'celeg, has left the city.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0004
rows.name: Bound for Noctilum, it seems.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0005
rows.name:
As for why she would head to a place filled with such
awful creatures, I have absolutely no idea.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0006
rows.name: And yet I feel incapable of simply letting her go.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0007
rows.name:
I see. Then this inscrutable emotional state is what you
humans call "worry."[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0008
rows.name:
I have good reason to worry, it would seem.
My division, Nen'celeg, has left the city.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0009
rows.name: She is apparently bound for Noctilum.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0010
rows.name:
As for why she would head to a place filled with such
awful creatures, I have absolutely no idea.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0011
rows.name:
I find the very concept as difficult to comprehend as this
new emotion of "worry."[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0012
rows.name:
I feel compelled to go forth and bring her back,
but I am a poor candidate to do so.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0013
rows.name:
Compared to the vicious wildlife of Mira,
the Orphe are poor combatants indeed.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0014
rows.name: Might I ask you to go after her in my stead?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0015
rows.name:
You humans are an extremely active and combative
species.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0016
rows.name:
I say that with a deep sense of what you humans call
gratitude.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0017
rows.name: Oh, and please take care that you are not injured.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0018
rows.name:
Though if you are injured somewhat in the course of
escorting my division, that is acceptable.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0019
rows.name:
I believe your kind call that a "trade-off."
Best of luck.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0030
rows.name: Accept

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0031
rows.name: Tell Nan'celeg that he can leave it to you.

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0040
rows.name: Chide

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0041
rows.name: Tell Nan'celeg that's a cold way of asking a favor.

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0020
rows.name:
Your attitude is most generous. That is the term you use
when describing someone who gives of themselves for
another, yes? Generous?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0021
rows.name: I wish you luck. Please bring my division back swiftly.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0022
rows.name:
I have heard of this. Humans sense temperature in
modes of phrasing, do they not?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0023
rows.name:
I will endeavor to use only the hottest of phrasings
in the future.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0024
rows.name:
This should yield the greatest motivation in your kind.
Now then... *ahem*[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0025
rows.name:
IT IS ALL ON YOU, [ST:gender p1=BRO p2=GIRL ]! YOU ARE THE BEST!
BRING NEN'CELEG HOME AND YOU WILL BE A
LEGEND FOREVER! OH YES, [ST:gender p1=BRO p2=GIRL ]![ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0026
rows.name:
...I assume you are sufficiently motivated now.
Please begin.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0027
rows.name: Please bring home my division, Nen'celeg.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0028
rows.name: Nen'celeg is safe, then. That is a relief.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0050
rows.name: Query

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0051
rows.name:
Ask Nan'celeg if he understands
"relief" better than "worry."

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0060
rows.name: Raise Eyebrows

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0061
rows.name: Express surprise that he remembered.

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0029
rows.name:
It is both the absence of worry, and its own emotional
state at the same time.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0030
rows.name:
I must say, all these fluctuations in psyche are most
illogical.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0031
rows.name:
Provided a supply of senirapa water, Nen'celeg's death
would present only a minor inconvenience.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0032
rows.name:
The Orphe's numbers would continue to grow just the
same.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0033
rows.name:
I could never forget.
Nen'celeg is one of us.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0034
rows.name:
In her absence, I was struck with a strange fluctuation
in my emotional state.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0035
rows.name:
Which is most strange, on further reflection.
Provided a supply of senirapa water, Nen'celeg's death
would present only a minor inconvenience.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0036
rows.name:
Perhaps I have dedicated excessive thought to
Nen'celeg's future.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0037
rows.name: Were you lonely with me gone?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0038
rows.name: Lonely? What is that?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0039
rows.name: Why would your absence cause me to feel...lonely?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0070
rows.name: Observe

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0071
rows.name: Say that it's because Nan'celeg is in love.

rows.label: qev055601_JNK0080
rows.name: Suggest

rows.label: qev055601_SEL0081
rows.name: Say that it's because Nen'celeg is a rare mutation.

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0040
rows.name:
Love? The phenomenon of attraction is exclusive to
species with distinct sexes.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0041
rows.name:
The Orphe have no such distinction, so there should be
no way that I would feel...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0042
rows.name:
Hmm. Yet I DO find Nen'celeg's appearance pleasing.
Almost...beautiful, as a human might say.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0043
rows.name: Is this attraction, then?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0044
rows.name: Nen'celeg? Am I attracted to you?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0045
rows.name:
Ask yourself that question! Species that experience love
call people like you dense.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0046
rows.name:
My density is comparable to most of the city's residents.
...Ah, wait. You mean slow-witted, then?
But I am comparatively intelligent. Most strange...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0049
rows.name:
That does make sense. But what is this strange array of
feelings I am experiencing?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0050
rows.name:
When I look at Nen'celeg, I find the sight pleasing.
Almost...beautiful, as a human might say.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0051
rows.name: It sounds as if you like me.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0052
rows.name: Like? ...Like. Do I like you, Nen'celeg?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0053
rows.name:
You do not know the answer for yourself?
Other species call people like you naive.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0054
rows.name: Naive? What a strange thing to say...[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0055
rows.name:
It is quite apparent that despite the Orphe's
considerable intelligence, some things remain
inscrutable.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0056
rows.name:
I do not understand my feelings for Nen'celeg.
But why not?[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0057
rows.name: Because you are naive.[ST:wait ]

rows.label: qev055601_MSG0058
rows.name:
Ah, I do not understand!
Grant me guidance, Ovah![ST:wait ]
